#: src/shell/shell.cpp:746
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_CHDIR_HELP"
msgid "Display or change the current directory.\n"
msgstr ""
"Affiche/change le répertoire courant.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:747
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_CHDIR_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]cd[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]chdir[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]  name of the directory to change to\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  Running [color=light-green]cd[reset] without an argument displays the current directory.\n"
"  With [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset] the command only changes the directory, not the current drive.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]cd[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]cd[reset] [color=light-cyan]mydir[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]cd[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]chdir[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]  nom du répertoire vers lequel se déplacer\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" Exécuter [color=light-green]cd[reset] sans argument affiche le répertoire courant.\n"
" Avec [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset], la commande change seulement le répertoire,\n"
" pas le lecteur courant.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]cd[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]cd[reset] [color=light-cyan]mydir[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:763
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_CLS_HELP"
msgid "Clear the DOS screen.\n"
msgstr ""
"Effacer l'écran.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:764
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_CLS_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]cls[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  This command has no parameters.\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  Running [color=light-green]cls[reset] clears all text on the DOS screen, except for the command\n"
"  prompt (e.g., [color=white]Z:\\>[reset] or [color=white]C:\\GAMES>[reset]) on the top-left corner of the screen.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]cls[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]cls[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" Cette commande n'a pas de paramètre.\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" L'exécution de [color=light-green]cls[reset] efface tout le texte affiché à l'écran DOS,\n"
" sauf l'invite de commande (ex. [color=white]Z:>[reset] ou [color=white]C:GAMES>[reset])\n"
" en haut à gauche.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]cls[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:778
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_DIR_HELP"
msgid "Display a list of files and subdirectories in a directory.\n"
msgstr ""
"Affiche une liste de fichiers et sous-répertoires dans un répertoire.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:780
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_DIR_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]dir[reset] [color=light-cyan][PATTERN][reset] [/w] \\[/b] [/p] [ad] [a-d] [/o[color=white]ORDER[reset]]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset]  either an exact filename or an inexact filename with wildcards, which\n"
"           are the asterisk (*) and the question mark (?); a path can be\n"
"           specified in the pattern to list contents in the specified directory\n"
"  [color=white]ORDER[reset]    listing order, including [color=white]n[reset] (by name, alphabetic), [color=white]s[reset] (by size,\n"
"           smallest first), [color=white]e[reset] (by extension, alphabetic), and [color=white]d[reset] (by date/time,\n"
"           oldest first), with an optional [color=white]-[reset] prefix to reverse order\n"
"  /w       list 5 files/directories in a row;  /b       list the names only\n"
"  /o[color=white]ORDER[reset]  order the list (see above);         /p       pause after each screen\n"
"  /ad      list all directories;               /a-d     list all files\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  Running [color=light-green]dir[reset] without an argument lists all files and subdirectories in the\n"
"  current directory, which is the same as [color=light-green]dir[reset] [color=light-cyan]*.*[reset].\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]dir[reset] [color=light-cyan][reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]dir[reset] [color=light-cyan]games.*[reset] /p\n"
"  [color=light-green]dir[reset] [color=light-cyan]c:\\games\\*.exe[reset] /b /o[color=white]-d[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]dir[reset] [color=light-cyan][PATTERN][reset] [/w] [/b] [/p] [ad] [a-d] [/o[color=white]ORDER[reset]]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset]  nom exact ou motif avec jokers (* et ?), avec chemin\n"
"          optionnel pour lister un répertoire donné\n"
" [color=white]ORDER[reset]    ordre d'affichage : [color=white]n[reset] (nom), [color=white]s[reset] (taille), [color=white]e[reset] (extension),\n"
"          [color=white]d[reset] (date/heure), avec préfixe [color=white]-[reset] pour inverser\n"
" /w       liste 5 entrées par ligne ;  /b       n'affiche que les noms\n"
" /o[color=white]ORDER[reset]  trié la liste ;               /p       pause à chaque écran\n"
" /ad      liste tous les répertoires ;      /a-d     liste tous les fichiers\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" Exécuter [color=light-green]dir[reset] sans argument liste tous les fichiers et\n"
" sous-répertoires du répertoire courant, équivalent à [color=light-green]dir[reset] [color=light-cyan]*.*[reset].\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]dir[reset] [color=light-cyan][reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]dir[reset] [color=light-cyan]games.*[reset] /p\n"
" [color=light-green]dir[reset] [color=light-cyan]c:games*.exe[reset] /b /o[color=white]-d[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:804
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_ECHO_HELP"
msgid "Display messages and enable/disable command echoing.\n"
msgstr ""
"Affiche des messages et active/désactive la commande ECHO.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:806
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_ECHO_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]echo[reset] [color=light-cyan][on|off][reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]echo[reset] [color=light-cyan][MESSAGE][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]on|off[reset]   turn on/off command echoing\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]MESSAGE[reset]  message to display\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - Running [color=light-green]echo[reset] without an argument shows the current on or off status.\n"
"  - Echo is especially useful when writing or debugging batch files.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]echo[reset] [color=light-cyan]off[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]echo[reset] [color=light-cyan]Hello world![reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]echo[reset] [color=light-cyan][on|off][reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]echo[reset] [color=light-cyan][MESSAGE][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]on|off[reset]   active/désactive l'écho des commandes\n"
" [color=light-cyan]MESSAGE[reset]  message à afficher\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" - Sans argument, [color=light-green]echo[reset] affiche l'état courant (on/off).\n"
" - ECHO est particulièrement utile dans les scripts batch, notamment en phase\n"
"   d'écriture ou de débogage.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]echo[reset] [color=light-cyan]off[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]echo[reset] [color=light-cyan]Hello world![reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:823
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_EXIT_HELP"
msgid "Exit from the DOS shell.\n"
msgstr ""
"Sortir du shell.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:824
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_EXIT_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]exit[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  This command has no parameters.\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  If you start a DOS shell from a program, running [color=light-green]exit[reset] returns to the program.\n"
"  If there is no DOS program running, the command quits from DOSBox Staging.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]exit[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]exit[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" Cette commande n'a pas de paramètre.\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" Si vous avez lancé un shell DOS depuis un programme, [color=light-green]exit[reset]\n"
" revient à ce programme. S'il n'y a pas de programme DOS en cours, la\n"
" commande quitte DOSBox Staging.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]exit[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:838
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_HELP_HELP"
msgid "Display help information for DOS commands.\n"
msgstr ""
"Montrer l'aide.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:840
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_HELP_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]help[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]help[reset] /a[ll]\n"
"  [color=light-green]help[reset] [color=light-cyan]COMMAND[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]COMMAND[reset]  name of an internal DOS command, such as [color=light-cyan]dir[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - Running [color=light-green]help[reset] without an argument displays a DOS command list.\n"
"  - You can view a full list of internal commands with the /a or /all option.\n"
"  - Instead of [color=light-green]help[reset] [color=light-cyan]COMMAND[reset], you can also get command help with [color=light-cyan]COMMAND[reset] /?.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]help[reset] [color=light-cyan]dir[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]help[reset] /all\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]help[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]help[reset] /a[ll]\n"
" [color=light-green]help[reset] [color=light-cyan]COMMAND[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]COMMAND[reset]  nom d'une commande DOS interne, par exemple [color=light-cyan]dir[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" - Sans argument, [color=light-green]help[reset] affiche une liste de commandes DOS.\n"
" - /a ou /all affiche la liste complète des commandes internes.\n"
" - Au lieu de [color=light-green]help[reset] [color=light-cyan]COMMAND[reset], vous pouvez aussi\n"
"   utiliser [color=light-cyan]COMMAND[reset] /?.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]help[reset] [color=light-cyan]dir[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]help[reset] /all\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:858
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_MKDIR_HELP"
msgid "Create a directory.\n"
msgstr ""
"Créer un répertoire.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:859
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_MKDIR_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]md[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]mkdir[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]  exact name of the directory to create\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - The directory must not exist yet.\n"
"  - You can specify a path where the directory will be created.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]md[reset] [color=light-cyan]newdir[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]md[reset] [color=light-cyan]c:\\games\\dir[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]md[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]mkdir[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]  nom exact du répertoire à créer\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" - Le répertoire ne doit pas déjà exister.\n"
" - Vous pouvez spécifier un chemin où créer le répertoire.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]md[reset] [color=light-cyan]newdir[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]md[reset] [color=light-cyan]c:gamesdir[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:875
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_RMDIR_HELP"
msgid "Remove a directory.\n"
msgstr ""
"Supprimer un répertoire.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:876
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_RMDIR_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]rd[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]rmdir[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]  name of the directory to remove\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  The directory must be empty, with no files or subdirectories.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]rd[reset] [color=light-cyan]emptydir[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]rd[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]rmdir[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY[reset]  nom du répertoire à supprimer\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" Le répertoire doit être vide, sans fichier ni sous-répertoire.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]rd[reset] [color=light-cyan]emptydir[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:890
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_SET_HELP"
msgid "Display or change environment variables.\n"
msgstr ""
"Changer les variables d'environnement.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:891
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_SET_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]set[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]set[reset] [color=white]VARIABLE[reset]=[color=light-cyan][STRING][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=white]VARIABLE[reset]  name of the environment variable\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]STRING[reset]    series of characters to assign to the variable\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - Assigning an empty string to the variable removes the variable.\n"
"  - The command without a parameter displays current environment variables.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]set[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]set[reset] [color=white]name[reset]=[color=light-cyan]value[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]set[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]set[reset] [color=white]VARIABLE[reset]=[color=light-cyan][STRING][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=white]VARIABLE[reset]  nom de la variable d'environnement\n"
" [color=light-cyan]STRING[reset]    chaîne de caractères à assigner\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" - Assigner une chaîne vide supprime la variable.\n"
" - Sans paramètre, la commande affiche les variables d'environnement actuelles.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]set[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]set[reset] [color=white]name[reset]=[color=light-cyan]value[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:908
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_IF_HELP"
msgid "Perform conditional processing in batch programs.\n"
msgstr ""
"Effectuer un processus avec condition dans les programmes batch.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:910
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_IF_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=light-magenta][not][reset] [color=light-cyan]errorlevel[reset] [color=white]NUMBER[reset] COMMAND\n"
"  [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=light-magenta][not][reset] [color=white]STR1==STR2[reset] COMMAND\n"
"  [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=light-magenta][not][reset] [color=light-cyan]exist[reset] [color=white]FILE[reset] COMMAND\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=white]NUMBER[reset]      positive integer less or equal to the desired value\n"
"  [color=white]STR1==STR2[reset]  compare two text strings (case-sensitive)\n"
"  [color=white]FILE[reset]        exact filename to check for existence\n"
"  COMMAND     DOS command or program to run, optionally with parameters\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - The COMMAND is run if any of the three conditions in the usage are met.\n"
"  - If [color=light-magenta]not[reset] is specified, then the command runs only with the false condition.\n"
"  - The [color=light-cyan]errorlevel[reset] condition is useful for checking if a programs ran correctly.\n"
"  - If either [color=white]STR1[reset] or [color=white]STR2[reset] may be empty, you can enclose them in quotes (\").\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=light-cyan]errorlevel[reset] [color=white]2[reset] dir\n"
"  [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=white]\"%%myvar%%\"==\"mystring\"[reset] echo Hello world!\n"
"  [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=light-magenta]not[reset] [color=light-cyan]exist[reset] [color=white]file.txt[reset] exit\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=light-magenta][not][reset] [color=light-cyan]errorlevel[reset] [color=white]NUMBER[reset] COMMAND\n"
" [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=light-magenta][not][reset] [color=white]STR1==STR2[reset] COMMAND\n"
" [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=light-magenta][not][reset] [color=light-cyan]exist[reset] [color=white]FILE[reset] COMMAND\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=white]NUMBER[reset]      entier positif inférieur ou égal à la valeur visée\n"
" [color=white]STR1==STR2[reset]  compare deux chaînes (sensible à la casse)\n"
" [color=white]FILE[reset]        nom exact du fichier à tester\n"
" COMMAND     commande DOS ou programme à lancer, avec paramètres optionnels\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" - COMMAND est exécutée si l'une des trois conditions est vraie.\n"
" - Si [color=light-magenta]not[reset] est présent, la commande s'exécute quand la condition est fausse.\n"
" - La condition [color=light-cyan]errorlevel[reset] est utile pour vérifier qu'un programme s'est bien\n"
"exécuté.\n"
" - Si [color=white]STR1[reset] ou [color=white]STR2[reset] peut être vide, placez-les entre guillemets (\").\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=light-cyan]errorlevel[reset] [color=white]2[reset] dir\n"
" [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=white]\"%%myvar%%\"==\"mystring\"[reset] echo Hello world!\n"
" [color=light-green]if[reset] [color=light-magenta]not[reset] [color=light-cyan]exist[reset] [color=white]file.txt[reset] exit\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:933
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_GOTO_HELP"
msgid "Jump to a labeled line in a batch program.\n"
msgstr ""
"Aller à la ligne de l'étiquette définie dans un script batch.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:935
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_GOTO_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]goto[reset] [color=light-cyan]LABEL[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]LABEL[reset]  text string used in the batch program as a label\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - A label is on a line by itself, beginning with a colon (:).\n"
"  - The label must be unique, and can be anywhere within the batch program.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]goto[reset] [color=light-cyan]mylabel[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]goto[reset] [color=light-cyan]LABEL[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]LABEL[reset]  chaîne utilisée comme étiquette dans le script batch\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" Une étiquette doit être seule sur sa ligne et commence par deux-points (:).\n"
" L'étiquette doit être unique et peut se trouver n'importe où dans le script.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]goto[reset] [color=light-cyan]mylabel[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:949
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_SHIFT_HELP"
msgid "Left-shift command-line parameters in a batch program.\n"
msgstr ""
"Décaler les paramètres de ligne de commande vers la gauche dans un script batch.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:950
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_SHIFT_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]shift[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  This command has no parameters.\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  This command allows a DOS batch program to accept more than 9 parameters.\n"
"  Running [color=light-green]shift[reset] left-shifts the batch program variable %%1 to %%0, %%2 to %%1, etc.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]shift[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]shift[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" Cette commande n'a pas de paramètre.\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" Cette commande permet à un script batch DOS d'accepter plus de 9 paramètres.\n"
" Exécuter [color=light-green]shift[reset] décale les variables batch vers la gauche : %%1 devient %%0,\n"
"%%2 devient %%1, etc.\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]shift[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:964
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_TYPE_HELP"
msgid "Display the contents of a text file.\n"
msgstr ""
"Affiche le contenu d'un fichier texte.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:965
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_TYPE_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]type[reset] [color=light-cyan]FILE[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]FILE[reset]  name of the file to display\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - The filename must be exact, optionally with a path.\n"
"  - This command is only for viewing text files, not binary files.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]type[reset] [color=light-cyan]text.txt[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]type[reset] [color=light-cyan]c:\\dos\\readme.txt[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]type[reset] [color=light-cyan]FILE[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]FILE[reset]  nom du fichier à afficher\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" - Le nom du fichier doit être exact, avec chemin optionnel.\n"
" - Cette commande sert uniquement à afficher des fichiers texte, pas des\n"
"   fichiers binaires.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]type[reset] [color=light-cyan]text.txt[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]type[reset] [color=light-cyan]c:\\dos\\readme.txt[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:980
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_REM_HELP"
msgid "Add comments in a batch program.\n"
msgstr ""
"Ajouter des commentaires dans un fichier batch.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:981
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_REM_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]rem[reset] [color=light-cyan]COMMENT[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]COMMENT[reset]  any comment you want to add\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - Adding comments to a batch program can make it easier to understand.\n"
"  - You can also temporarily comment out some commands with this command.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]rem[reset] [color=light-cyan]This is my test batch program.[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]rem[reset] [color=light-cyan]COMMENT[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]COMMENT[reset]  commentaire à ajouter\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" - Ajouter des commentaires dans un script batch en facilite la compréhension.\n"
" - Cette commande permet aussi de commenter temporairement certaines commandes.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]rem[reset] [color=light-cyan]This is my test batch program.[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:995
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_NO_WILD"
msgid "This is a simple version of the command, no wildcards allowed!\n"
msgstr ""
"C'est une version simple de la commande, aucun joker autorisé !\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:997
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_RENAME_HELP"
msgid "Rename one or more files.\n"
msgstr ""
"Renomme un ou plusieurs fichiers.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:998
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_RENAME_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]ren[reset] [color=white]SOURCE[reset] [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]rename[reset] [color=white]SOURCE[reset] [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=white]SOURCE[reset]       name of the file to rename\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset]  new name for the renamed file\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - The source filename must be exact, optionally with a path.\n"
"  - The destination filename must be exact without a path.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]ren[reset] [color=white]oldname[reset] [color=light-cyan]newname[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]ren[reset] [color=white]c:\\dos\\file.txt[reset] [color=light-cyan]f.txt[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"RENAME [lecteur:][chemin]nomfichier1 nomfichier2.\n"
"EN [lecteur:][chemin]nomfichier1 nomfichier2.\n"
"\n"
"Notez que vous ne pouvez pas spécifier un nouveau lecteur ou chemin pourvotre\n"
"ichier cible.\n"
"\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1015
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_DELETE_HELP"
msgid "Remove one or more files.\n"
msgstr ""
"Supprimer un ou plusieurs fichiers.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1016
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_DELETE_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]del[reset] [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]erase[reset] [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset]  either an exact filename (such as [color=light-cyan]file.txt[reset]) or an inexact filename\n"
"           using one or more wildcards, which are the asterisk (*) representing\n"
"           any sequence of one or more characters, and the question mark (?)\n"
"           representing any single character, such as [color=light-cyan]*.bat[reset] and [color=light-cyan]c?.txt[reset].\n"
"\n"
"Warning:\n"
"  Be careful when using a pattern with wildcards, especially [color=light-cyan]*.*[reset], as all files\n"
"  matching the pattern will be deleted.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]del[reset] [color=light-cyan]test.bat[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]del[reset] [color=light-cyan]c*.*[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]del[reset] [color=light-cyan]a?b.c*[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]del[reset] [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]erase[reset] [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset]  nom de fichier exact (par ex. [color=light-cyan]file.txt[reset]) ou\n"
"            motif avec un ou plusieurs jokers : * pour une séquence\n"
"            d'un ou plusieurs caractères, ? pour un seul caractère\n"
"            (par ex. [color=light-cyan]*.bat[reset], [color=light-cyan]c?.txt[reset]).\n"
"\n"
"vertissement :\n"
" Soyez prudent avec les motifs à jokers, surtout [color=light-cyan]*.*[reset], car tous les\n"
" fichiers correspondants seront supprimés.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]del[reset] [color=light-cyan]test.bat[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]del[reset] [color=light-cyan]c*.*[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]del[reset] [color=light-cyan]a?b.c*[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1036
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_COPY_HELP"
msgid "Copy one or more files.\n"
msgstr ""
"Copier des fichiers.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1037
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_COPY_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]copy[reset] [color=white]SOURCE[reset] [color=light-cyan][DESTINATION][reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]copy[reset] [color=white]SOURCE1+SOURCE2[+...][reset] [color=light-cyan][DESTINATION][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=white]SOURCE[reset]       either an exact filename or an inexact filename with wildcards,\n"
"               which are the asterisk (*) and the question mark (?)\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset]  exact filename or directory, not containing any wildcards\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - The [color=white]+[reset] operator combines multiple source files provided to a single file.\n"
"  - [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset] is optional: if omitted, files are copied to the current path.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]copy[reset] [color=white]source.bat[reset] [color=light-cyan]new.bat[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]copy[reset] [color=white]file1.txt+file2.txt[reset] [color=light-cyan]file3.txt[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]copy[reset] [color=white]..\\c*.*[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]copy[reset] [color=white]SOURCE[reset] [color=light-cyan][DESTINATION][reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]copy[reset] [color=white]SOURCE1+SOURCE2[+...][reset] [color=light-cyan][DESTINATION][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=white]SOURCE[reset]       nom exact de fichier ou motif avec jokers (* et ?)\n"
" [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset]  nom exact de fichier ou de répertoire (sans joker)\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" L'opérateur [color=white]+[reset] concatène plusieurs fichiers source en un seul fichier.\n"
" La destination est optionnelle : si omise, la copie se fait vers le chemin\n"
"ourant.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]copy[reset] [color=white]source.bat[reset] [color=light-cyan]new.bat[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]copy[reset] [color=white]file1.txt+file2.txt[reset] [color=light-cyan]file3.txt[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]copy[reset] [color=white]..c*.*[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1056
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_CALL_HELP"
msgid "Start a batch program from within another batch program.\n"
msgstr ""
"Lancer un fichier batch à partir d'un autre fichier batch..\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1058
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_CALL_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]call[reset] [color=white]BATCH[reset] [color=light-cyan][PARAMETERS][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=white]BATCH[reset]       batch program to launch\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]PARAMETERS[reset]  optional parameters for the batch program\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  After calling another batch program, the original batch program will resume\n"
"  running after the other batch program ends.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]call[reset] [color=white]mybatch.bat[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]call[reset] [color=white]file.bat[reset] [color=light-cyan]Hello world![reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]call[reset] [color=white]BATCH[reset] [color=light-cyan][PARAMETERS][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=white]BATCH[reset]       script batch à lancer\n"
" [color=light-cyan]PARAMETERS[reset]  paramètres optionnels du script batch\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" Après l'appel d'un autre script batch, le script d'origine reprend son\n"
" exécution une fois l'autre script terminé.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]call[reset] [color=white]mybatch.bat[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]call[reset] [color=white]file.bat[reset] [color=light-cyan]Hello world![reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1073
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_SUBST_HELP"
msgid "Assign an internal directory to a drive.\n"
msgstr ""
"Assigner un répertoire interne à un lecteur.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1074
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_SUBST_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]subst[reset] [color=white]DRIVE[reset] [color=light-cyan]PATH[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]subst[reset] [color=white]DRIVE[reset] /d\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=white]DRIVE[reset]  drive to which you want to assign a path\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]PATH[reset]   mounted DOS path you want to assign to\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - The path must be on a drive mounted by the [color=light-green]mount[reset] command.\n"
"  - You can remove an assigned drive with the /d option.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]subst[reset] [color=white]d:[reset] [color=light-cyan]c:\\games[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]subst[reset] [color=white]e:[reset] [color=light-cyan]/d[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]subst[reset] [color=white]DRIVE[reset] [color=light-cyan]PATH[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]subst[reset] [color=white]DRIVE[reset] /d\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=white]DRIVE[reset]  lecteur auquel associer un chemin\n"
" [color=light-cyan]PATH[reset]   chemin DOS monté à associer\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" Le chemin doit se trouver sur un lecteur monté via la commande [color=light-green]mount[reset].\n"
" L'option /d permet de supprimer une association existante.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]subst[reset] [color=white]d:[reset] [color=light-cyan]c:games[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]subst[reset] [color=white]e:[reset] [color=light-cyan]/d[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1091
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_LOADHIGH_HELP"
msgid "Load a DOS program into upper memory.\n"
msgstr ""
"Charger un programme en mémoire haute (requiert xms=true et umb=true).\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1092
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_LOADHIGH_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]lh[reset] [color=light-cyan]PROGRAM[reset] [color=white][PARAMETERS][reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]loadhigh[reset] [color=light-cyan]PROGRAM[reset] [color=white][PARAMETERS][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]PROGRAM[reset]  DOS TSR program to load, optionally with parameters\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  This command intends to save the conventional memory by loading specified DOS\n"
"  TSR programs into upper memory if possible. Such programs may be required for\n"
"  some DOS games; XMS and UMB memory must be enabled (xms=true and umb=true).\n"
"  Not all DOS TSR programs can be loaded into upper memory with this command.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]lh[reset] [color=light-cyan]tsrapp[reset] [color=white]args[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]lh[reset] [color=light-cyan]PROGRAM[reset] [color=white][PARAMETERS][reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]loadhigh[reset] [color=light-cyan]PROGRAM[reset] [color=white][PARAMETERS][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]PROGRAM[reset]  programme TSR DOS à charger, éventuellement avec paramètres\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" Cette commande vise à économiser la mémoire conventionnelle en chargeant,\n"
" si possible, des TSR DOS en mémoire haute. Ces programmes peuvent être\n"
" nécessaires pour certains jeux DOS ; les mémoires XMS et UMB doivent être\n"
" activées (xms=true et umb=true).\n"
" Tous les TSR DOS ne peuvent pas être chargés en mémoire haute via cette\n"
" commande.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]lh[reset] [color=light-cyan]tsrapp[reset] [color=white]args[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1109
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_ATTRIB_HELP"
msgid "Display or change file attributes.\n"
msgstr ""
"Ne fait rien. Fourni pour la compatibilité.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1111
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_ATTRIB_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]attrib[reset] [color=white][ATTRIBUTES][reset] [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset] [/S]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=white]ATTRIBUTES[reset]  attributes to apply, including one or more of the following:\n"
"              [color=white]+R[reset], [color=white]-R[reset], [color=white]+A[reset], [color=white]-A[reset], [color=white]+S[reset], [color=white]-S[reset], [color=white]+H[reset], [color=white]-H[reset]\n"
"              where: R = Read-only, A = Archive, S = System, H = Hidden\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset]     either an exact filename or an inexact filename with wildcards,\n"
"              which are the asterisk (*) and the question mark (?), or an exact\n"
"              name of a directory\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - Multiple attributes can be specified in the command, separated by spaces.\n"
"  - If not specified, the command shows the current file/directory attributes.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]attrib[reset] [color=light-cyan]file.txt[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]attrib[reset] [color=white]+R[reset] [color=white]-A[reset] [color=light-cyan]*.txt[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]attrib[reset] [color=white][ATTRIBUTES][reset] [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset] [/S]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=white]ATTRIBUTES[reset]  attributs à appliquer, un ou plusieurs parmi :\n"
"             [color=white]+R[reset], [color=white]-R[reset], [color=white]+A[reset], [color=white]-A[reset], [color=white]+S[reset], [color=white]-S[reset], [color=white]+H[reset], [color=white]-H[reset]\n"
"             où : R = Lecture seule, A = Archive, S = Système, H = Caché\n"
" [color=light-cyan]PATTERN[reset]     nom exact de fichier, motif avec jokers (* et ?),\n"
"             ou nom exact de répertoire\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" - Plusieurs attributs peuvent être indiqués, séparés par des espaces.\n"
" - Sans attribut, la commande affiche les attributs actuels des fichiers ou\n"
"épertoires.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]attrib[reset] [color=light-cyan]file.txt[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]attrib[reset] [color=white]+R[reset] [color=white]-A[reset] [color=light-cyan]*.txt[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1130
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_ATTRIB_GET_ERROR"
msgid "Unable to get attributes: %s\n"
msgstr ""
"Impossible de lire les attributs : %s\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1131
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_ATTRIB_SET_ERROR"
msgid "Unable to set attributes: %s\n"
msgstr ""
"Impossible de définir les attributs : %s\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1133
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_CHOICE_HELP"
msgid "Wait for a keypress and set an ERRORLEVEL value.\n"
msgstr ""
"Attendre l'appui sur une touche et définir le ERRORLEVEL.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1135
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_CHOICE_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]choice[reset] [color=light-cyan][TEXT][reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]choice[reset] /c[:][color=white]CHOICES[reset] /n /s /t[:][color=white]c[reset],[color=light-magenta]nn[reset] [color=light-cyan][TEXT][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]TEXT[reset]          text to display as a prompt, or empty\n"
"  /c[:][color=white]CHOICES[reset]  specify allowable keys, which default to [color=white]yn[reset]\n"
"  /n            do not display the choices at end of prompt\n"
"  /s            enable case-sensitive choices to be selected\n"
"  /t[:][color=white]c[reset],[color=light-magenta]nn[reset]     choose [color=white]c[reset] by default after [color=light-magenta]nn[reset] seconds\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  This command sets an ERRORLEVEL value starting from 1 according to the\n"
"  allowable keys specified in /c option, and the user input can then be checked\n"
"  with the [color=light-green]if[reset] command. With /n option only the specified text will be displayed,\n"
"  but not the actual choices (such as the default [color=white][Y,N]?[reset]) in the end.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]choice[reset] /t:[color=white]y[reset],[color=light-magenta]2[reset] [color=light-cyan]Continue[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]choice[reset] /c:[color=white]abc[reset] /s [color=light-cyan]Type the letter a, b, or c[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"CHOICE [/C:choix] [/N] [/S] texte\n"
" /C[:]choix  -  Spécifie les touches utilisables. Par défaut : yn(oui/non).\n"
" /N  -  N'affiche pas les choix à la fin du prompt.\n"
" /S  -  Active la sensibilité à la casse des choix.\n"
" texte  -  Texte à afficher comme prompt.\n"
"\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1156
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_CHOICE_EOF"
msgid ""
"\n"
"[color=light-red]Choice failed[reset]: the input stream ended without a valid choice.\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"[color=light-red]Échec de CHOICE[reset] : le flux d'entrée s'est terminé sans choix valide.\n"
"\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1157
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_CHOICE_ABORTED"
msgid ""
"\n"
"[color=yellow]Choice aborted.[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"[color=yellow]CHOICE interrompu.[reset]\n"
"\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1159
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_PATH_HELP"
msgid "Display or set a search path for executable files.\n"
msgstr ""
"Fourni pour la compatibilité.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1161
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_PATH_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]path[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]path[reset] [color=light-cyan][[DRIVE:]PATH[;...]][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan][[DRIVE:]PATH[;...]][reset]  path(s) containing a drive and directory\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - More than one path can be specified, separated by a semi-colon (;).\n"
"  - Parameter with only a semi-colon (;) clears all search path settings.\n"
"  - The path can also be set using the [color=light-green]set[reset] command, e.g. [color=light-green]set[reset] [color=white]path[reset]=[color=light-cyan]Z:\\[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]path[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]path[reset] [color=light-cyan]Z:\\;C:\\DOS[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]path[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]path[reset] [color=light-cyan][[DRIVE:]PATH[;...]][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan][[DRIVE:]PATH[;...]][reset]  un ou plusieurs chemins (lecteur + répertoire)\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" - Plusieurs chemins peuvent être fournis, séparés par des points-virgules (;).\n"
" - Un seul paramètre ';' efface toute la configuration du chemin de recherche.\n"
" - Le chemin peut aussi être défini avec [color=light-green]set[reset], par exemple [color=light-green]set[reset] [color=white]path[reset]=[color=light-cyan]Z:[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]path[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]path[reset] [color=light-cyan]Z:;C:DOS[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1178
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_VER_HELP"
msgid "Display the DOS version.\n"
msgstr ""
"Voir ou régler la version de DOS reportée.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1179
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_VER_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]ver[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - The DOS version can be set in the configuration file under the [dos]\n"
"    section, using the 'ver = [color=light-cyan]VERSION[reset]' setting.\n"
"  - The DOS version reported to applications can be changed using the [color=light-green]setver[reset]\n"
"    command.\n"
"  - The old '[color=light-green]ver[reset] [color=white]set[reset] [color=light-cyan]VERSION[reset]' syntax to change the DOS version is deprecated.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]ver[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation :\n"
" [color=light-green]ver[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]ver[reset] [color=white]set[reset] [color=light-cyan]VERSION[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Avec :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]VERSION[reset] peut être un entier, comme [color=light-cyan]5[reset], ou inclure une décimale\n"
"         à deux chiffres, comme [color=light-cyan]6.22[reset], [color=light-cyan]7.01[reset] ou [color=light-cyan]7.10[reset]. Les décimales\n"
"         peuvent aussi être séparées par un espace, comme [color=light-cyan]622[reset], [color=light-cyan]7 01[reset] ou [color=light-cyan]7 10[reset].\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" La version de DOS peut aussi être réglée dans le fichier de configuration\n"
" sous la section [dos], via le paramètre 'ver = [color=light-cyan]VERSION[reset]'.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]ver[reset] [color=white]set[reset] [color=light-cyan]6.22[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]ver[reset] [color=white]set[reset] [color=light-cyan]710[reset]\n"
"\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1192
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_VER_VER"
msgid ""
"DOSBox Staging version %s\n"
"DOS version %d.%02d\n"
msgstr ""
"DOSBox Staging version %s\n"
"DOS version %d.%02d\n"
"\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1194
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_VER_INVALID"
msgid "The specified DOS version is not correct.\n"
msgstr ""
"La version spécifiée de DOS n'est pas correcte.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1196
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_VOL_HELP"
msgid "Display the disk volume and serial number, if they exist.\n"
msgstr "Affiche l'étiquette de volume du disque."

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1198
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_VOL_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]vol[reset] [color=light-cyan][DRIVE:][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]DRIVE[reset]  drive letter followed by a colon\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  Running [color=light-green]vol[reset] without an argument uses the current drive.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]vol[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]vol[reset] [color=light-cyan]c:[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Usage :\n"
" [color=light-green]vol[reset] [color=light-cyan][LECTEUR:][reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=light-cyan]LECTEUR[reset]  lettre de lecteur suivie d'un deux-points\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" Lancez [color=light-green]vol[reset] sans argument pour utiliser le lecteur\n"
" courant.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]vol[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]vol[reset] [color=light-cyan]c:[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1211
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_VOL_OUTPUT"
msgid ""
"\n"
" Volume in drive %c is %s\n"
" Volume Serial Number is %04X-%04X\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"Le volume du lecteur %c est %s\n"
"Le numero de série du volume est %04X-%04X\n"
"\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1217
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_MOVE_HELP"
msgid "Move files and rename files and directories.\n"
msgstr ""
"Déplace des fichiers et renomme des fichiers et des répertoires.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1219
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_MOVE_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]move[reset] [color=white]FILENAME1[,FILENAME2,...][reset] [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]move[reset] [color=white]DIRECTORY1[reset] [color=light-cyan]DIRECTORY2[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=white]FILENAME[reset]     either an exact filename or an inexact filename with wildcards,\n"
"               which are the asterisk (*) and the question mark (?);\n"
"               multiple, comma-separated, filenames can be provided\n"
"  [color=white]DIRECTORY[reset]    exact directory name, not containing any wildcards\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset]  exact filename or directory, not containing any wildcards\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - If multiple source files are specified, [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset] must be a directory.\n"
"    If not, one will be created for you.\n"
"  - If a single source file is specified, it will overwrite [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset].\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]move[reset] [color=white]source.bat[reset] [color=light-cyan]new.bat[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]move[reset] [color=white]file1.txt,file2.txt[reset] [color=light-cyan]mydir[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Usage :\n"
" [color=light-green]move[reset] [color=white]FICHIER1[,FICHIER2,...][reset] [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]move[reset] [color=white]REPERTOIRE1[reset] [color=light-cyan]REPERTOIRE2[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=white]FICHIER[reset]      soit un nom exact, soit un nom avec\n"
"               jokers (astérisque (*) et point d'interrogation (?)) ;\n"
"               plusieurs noms séparés par des virgules sont acceptés\n"
" [color=white]REPERTOIRE[reset]   nom exact de répertoire, sans joker\n"
" [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset]  fichier ou répertoire exact, sans joker\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" - Si plusieurs fichiers source sont spécifiés,\n"
"   [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset] doit être un répertoire.\n"
"   Sinon, un répertoire sera créé.\n"
" - Si un seul fichier source est spécifié, il écrasera\n"
"   [color=light-cyan]DESTINATION[reset].\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]move[reset] [color=white]source.bat[reset] [color=light-cyan]new.bat[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]move[reset] [color=white]file1.txt,file2.txt[reset] [color=light-cyan]mydir[reset]\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1239
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_MOVE_MULTIPLE_TO_SINGLE"
msgid "Cannot move multiple files to a single file.\n"
msgstr ""
"Impossible de déplacer plusieurs fichiers vers un seul fichier.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1241
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_FOR_HELP"
msgid "Run a specified command for each string in a set.\n"
msgstr ""
"Exécute une commande spécifiée pour chaque chaîne d'un ensemble.\n"

#: src/shell/shell.cpp:1243
#, c-format, no-wrap
msgctxt "SHELL_CMD_FOR_HELP_LONG"
msgid ""
"Usage:\n"
"  [color=light-green]for[reset] [color=white]%%VAR[reset] [color=light-cyan]in[reset] [color=white](SET)[reset] [color=light-cyan]do[reset] [color=white]COMMAND[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Parameters:\n"
"  [color=white]%%VAR[reset]     single character representing a variable, prefixed by a '%%'\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]in[reset]       case-insensitive keyword\n"
"  [color=white](SET)[reset]    set of strings to replace [color=white]%%VAR[reset] instances in [color=white]COMMAND[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-cyan]do[reset]       case-insensitive keyword\n"
"  [color=white]COMMAND[reset]  command to repeat for each string in [color=white](SET)[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Notes:\n"
"  - In batch files, [color=white]%%VAR[reset] must be written as [color=white]%%VAR[reset] (two percent signs) instead.\n"
"  - Strings in [color=white](SET)[reset] may be separated by any valid DOS separator.\n"
"  - Any string in [color=white](SET)[reset] containing wildcards (* or ?) will expand to\n"
"    the set of matching files in the current directory.\n"
"  - Using another [color=light-green]for[reset] command as [color=white]COMMAND[reset] is not permitted.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  [color=light-green]for[reset] [color=white]%%C[reset] [color=light-cyan]in[reset] [color=white](ONE TWO)[reset] [color=light-cyan]do[reset] [color=white]MKDIR[reset] [color=white]%%C[reset]\n"
"  [color=light-green]for[reset] [color=white]%%D[reset] [color=light-cyan]in[reset] [color=white](*.TXT)[reset] [color=light-cyan]do[reset] [color=white]ECHO[reset] [color=white]%%D[reset]\n"
msgstr ""
"Usage :\n"
" [color=light-green]for[reset] [color=white]%%VAR[reset] [color=light-cyan]in[reset] [color=white](ENSEMBLE)[reset] [color=light-cyan]do[reset] [color=white]COMMANDE[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Paramètres :\n"
" [color=white]%%VAR[reset]     caractère unique représentant une variable, préfixé par '%%'\n"
" [color=light-cyan]in[reset]       mot-clé insensible à la casse\n"
" [color=white](ENSEMBLE)[reset] ensemble de chaînes remplaçant [color=white]%%VAR[reset] dans [color=white]COMMANDE[reset]\n"
" [color=light-cyan]do[reset]       mot-clé insensible à la casse\n"
" [color=white]COMMANDE[reset] commande répétée pour chaque chaîne de [color=white](ENSEMBLE)[reset]\n"
"\n"
"Notes :\n"
" - Dans les fichiers batch, [color=white]%%VAR[reset] doit être écrit [color=white]%%VAR[reset] (deux signes %%).\n"
" - Les chaînes dans [color=white](ENSEMBLE)[reset] peuvent être séparées par tout séparateur DOS\n"
"   valide.\n"
" - Toute chaîne de [color=white](ENSEMBLE)[reset] contenant des jokers (* ou ?) est étendue\n"
"   à l'ensemble des fichiers correspondants dans le répertoire courant.\n"
" - L'utilisation d'une autre commande [color=light-green]for[reset] comme [color=white]COMMANDE[reset] n'est pas autorisée.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
" [color=light-green]for[reset] [color=white]%%C[reset] [color=light-cyan]in[reset] [color=white](ONE TWO)[reset] [color=light-cyan]do[reset] [color=white]MKDIR[reset] [color=white]%%C[reset]\n"
" [color=light-green]for[reset] [color=white]%%D[reset] [color=light-cyan]in[reset] [color=white](*.TXT)[reset] [color=light-cyan]do[reset] [color=white]ECHO[reset] [color=white]%%D[reset]\n"

